      "id": 14,
      "options": {
        "content": "\n# CIS benchmarking tests, implemented by kube-bench\n\nThese tests are specified by CIS and implemented by kube-bench, see more information (such as descriptions of the different tests) about CIS [here](https://www.cisecurity.org/benchmark/kubernetes/) and kube-bench [here](https://github.com/aquasecurity/kube-bench).\n\nAutomatic vs manual tests: CIS have determined that some tests can be run automatically, kube-bench have additionally turned some manual tests into automatic ones. In this dashboard the manual tests (as per kube-bench) are only included in the table at the bottom.\n\nScored vs non-scored: scored tests are the test CIS chose as automatic, non-scored test are the manual tests that kube-bench made automatic. Non-scored might not fit as many kubernetes setups and are thus only classified as warnings if they fail.\n",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
